Class ConvexHullAlgorithm

java.lang.Object
  ConvexHullAlgorithm
Direct Known Subclasses:
AnimationExample, GiftWrapper, GrahamScanner
public abstract class ConvexHullAlgorithm
extends java.lang.Object

To implement different convex hull algorithms, this class should be extended and the convesHull() method should be implemented. Subclasses may add animations by using the drawPoint(), deletePoint(), drawSegment(), and deleteSegment() methods. After calling some number of these methods, calling refreshDisplay() will make the changes visible.

Author:
Justin Johnson

convexHull

public abstract java.util.List<Point> convexHull(java.util.Set<Point> points)
Computes the convex hull of a set of points. Subclasses must implement this method.

Parameters:
points - The points for which the convex hull is to be computed.
Returns:
A List containing the convex hull of the input set, where the points are ordered either clockwise or counterclockwise around the bounding polygon.
